<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-085-078  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 085 078.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  Feb 20 1989 n526 p69(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Japan's opto industry soars 20%. (optoelectronics)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Sakurai, Miyoko.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The optoelectronics industry in Japan is expected to total morethan $15 billion by the time the fiscal year ends on March 31,1989.andP;  This is a 20 percent jump over the previous year.andP;  Themarket for rewriteable optical disk drives alone should total morethen $115 million.andP;  The Optoelectronics Industry and TechnologyDevelopment Association divides the industry into three areas:optical components, optical equipment and optoelectronic appliedsystems.andP;  Optical equipment should show a 23 percent growth rate.andO;The optical components sector is expected to increase 14 percent.andO;Applied systems should show an eight percent increase.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     JapanOptoelectronic DevicesOptical DisksOpticsIndustry Analysis.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>